##World Champion volunteer road back home: from being told to put away your Wuhan Id, to saluting a child

Micro Signal txsports

Introduction of functions, official account of tencent sports channel

The following article is from tencent frontier, by Xu Sijia

"though there is a limit, there is no end. ". Frontier is the original column of deep sports built by tencent sports. Take you within the boundaries of Sports, interpretation of news events, declassification of the truth, deconstruction of sports time and space. Here, not just at the scene.

From persuading you to put away your Wuhan ID card and mocking you for making money by volunteering to buy goods, to children saluting you and villagers smiling at you, wrestling world champion Xu Qing has learned how far and near people can be, from overwhelmed to full and warm inside. As she felt, the more difficult the moment, the more each of us has to take a step forward, each small step will bring more confidence to the other side. This is the story of wrestling world champion Xu Qing, the third part of tencent sports'original plan, me and my city.

I'm Xu Qing, a retired wrestler. I was the women's Wrestling World Cup champion in 2008 and 2011, but when most people hear my name, they instinctively say, "so you have the same name as Xu Qing! "

During the more than a month when the epidemic of new crown pneumonia was raging, I became a grass-roots epidemic prevention volunteer in my hometown village, handing out leaflets, purchasing materials, registering personnel information, contacting and checking mobile personnel, and body temperature statistics, every day in the busy and enrichment feel the crisis of the moment to be trusted, to be satisfied with the needs.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
##01

##20 years of sports. This is the first time I've spent this much time at home

I was born in a small village in Haokou town, Qianjiang, Hubei Province, and now I work in Wuhan. I have been practicing sports for 20 years since I started playing for Hubei team at the age of 14. Accustomed to traveling and preparing for war, I have never stayed so long in my hometown.

In 2003's SARS, at that time I just at the beginning of the year followed the Hubei team to the North Body big tryout, the coach worried that I was too young to take me to live together outside the school. Later, I remember that because of the outbreak in Beijing, the whole school was closed, we had to rush back to Wuhan, where we were quarantined again, and the smell of biscuits, instant noodles and disinfectant became the most vivid memories of that time.

I've been out of the service twice in my life.

During a training session before the 2013 National Games, I ruptured a medial ligament in my knee joint during a confrontation with a male posterior cruciate ligament. The game is coming up, and between the surgery and the game, I chose to stick with it, and I've worked too long to let it go to waste. As a result, I finished fourth, the cruelest place for an athlete, because the podium was right in front of you and you couldn't reach it.

After that, I chose to study abroad and completed ten months of study in the United States. Before the 2017 National Games, I chose to come back. The ideal is beautiful, but the reality is difficult to move. As a result of the class reform, I could not find suitable rival training in Hubei Women's wrestling team. I had to go to the men's team to train. The men are fast. Once, my head on the ground, fell to the ground, the head and body are all Numb, half a day to get up. Check found that the injury to the neck of the nerve roots, left side of the body loss of consciousness, left hand can not even hold up the pole.

Old Injury plus new injury, a lot of people do not believe that I participate in the National Games. But I can't take no for an answer. Every day before training to go to the infirmary acupuncture treatment, from the neck to finger a day is more than 20 needles. Training can not fall on the actual battle to train strength, restore to maintain physical fitness to go running, a day to adhere to down, spare time spent on an analysis of the opponent.

Finally, I survived, created the Hubei Women's wrestling team in the National Games of the best results.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That year, during the preparation for the National Games, I applied for the Hubei Provincial Sports Bureau civil servant, passed the written examination, interview, and was finally hired, stay in Wuhan to work.

After the retirement of me, did not leave the sports of the old profession, I like this rhythm, for a game busy, for a small goal to persist. Besides, now I can finally go home for Chinese New Year.

So many years did not go home, the village house is high, road width, once the neighbors have not recognized me.

People in my hometown like lively, love to visit the New Year, banquet, playing Mahjong, this Spring Festival is not seen. Back home, I deliberately put the family that Mahjong also put away, for this, but also almost quarrel with the elders.

It's funny how different the flavors are.

##02

##Panic and helplessness: two days before the closure of the city through the Hankou Railway Station, Wechat learned that the sister Shi family infection

February 3, was originally the Tokyo Olympic Games boxing events in the Asian region of the qualification match held in Wuhan. Our colleagues in the competition department began to prepare very early, in order to meet the competition, we will return to Wuhan to prepare for the fourth day of the competition work, so changed the rest, two days early home for the New Year.

On January 21, I passed by the Hankou Railway Station on my way home for the Spring Festival. By the time he got off the bus, academician Zhong Nanshan had visited his friend as if a new virus had confirmed human to human transmission.

I was so scared when I got home. I can't stop going over every detail of my Hankou Railway Station. I looked around at my family and my little niece, and I couldn't stop freaking out. Random Thoughts was out of control, and I had no idea how to deal with what was coming.

My father locked the iron gate of the yard, closed the door for visitors, and my relatives only shouted at me through the yard door.

On January 23, the city of Wuhan was closed. My heart is filled with mixed emotions, I am glad I have left the city and can not help but worry about the body, missing Wuhan Relatives and friends... at a loss.

The day after the city was sealed was New Year's Eve. I have received many blessings and greetings from friends from other places on Wechat. Some friends who have not contacted me for a long time have also sent messages. Some friends who are abroad have asked me if I need supplies and colleagues in the work group, everyone's greetings turned into numbers reporting body temperature. On special days, it's easy to be warm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan after the blockade

Since the outbreak, I have been afraid to micro-blog, I dare not face the rising cold figures and the sweat and tears of health care workers. But I pay close attention to my friend circle every day, because I am really worried about what will happen to my friends in Wuhan.

Until that day, I learned from the circle of friends, the wrestling team's sister-in-law family, are infected. I muddled, in the dialog box of the typing and deleted, I do not know how to comfort sister, outside the siege of Wuhan, I like the fist hit the cotton, strong but not out.

I could only comfort her and cheer her up, "please get well soon! I want to eat my aunt's dumplings! Our lobster is coming to market in Qianjiang, when are you coming, I invite you to my house! " I thought, perhaps the mood is a little more relaxed, the body will be a lot better!

On the night of February 3, the Wembley Arena under the Hubei Sports Bureau received a notice to renovate the "shelter hospital, " and many colleagues in the system who were stranded in Wuhan became volunteers. After an all-nighter, it was transformed into an 800-bed "shelter hospital" waiting for patients with mild cases of COVID-19 pneumonia.

At that moment, I sincerely admire my colleagues, but also proud of them!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Wembley Arena is a shelter hospital

##03

##Grass-roots epidemic prevention volunteers'understanding: the value of life is to be needed

Home Isolation of 14 days, I often lay in bed alone in a daze, somewhat dazed, depressed. Thinking, if you can do something, to be able to help a little bit, better than nothing to do, at least you will feel that they are needed.

There are only 6 village cadres in our village. To serve 10 village groups, village cadres need to use loudspeakers to publicize, hand out leaflets, check roadblocks, perform duties at intersections, purchase materials, maintain order, register personnel, and coordinate with neighbors. Then, as soon as I was out of quarantine, I thought of reporting to the village committee and applying to be involved in the prevention and control of the epidemic in the village.

Today, I am mainly responsible for the village of a group and 10 groups of villagers living supplies procurement. Visit 56 families in two village groups every day, count the necessities, go door to door to ask, confirm, distribute, a trip down about three hours, every morning at 9 am to go out to 5 pm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Qing's daily stats

In order to prevent and control the epidemic, the village road is closed, leaving only the rugged path. Plus I was away from the village all the year round, and people and roads were unfamiliar. My father would drive a "open car" with me every day to deliver the goods. My brother and brother would also help carry them. My grandmother and mother would prepare meals every day so that we could safely serve the villagers, even little nieces have a job to do: Entertain and cheer up the family when they are too tired to do anything.

From rice and oil to underwear, diapers and hard-luck sugar cane, daily purchases of a variety of things, filled with a few tricycles. Sometimes, the delivery of tricycles parked on the side of the road, a pay no attention, but found that the car has been in the river ditch, a line of people have to pull the cart, "rescue" supplies.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Qing's supplies for the villagers

As a volunteer in the field, a lot of people say I'm helping people, but they're helping me, too. Many times, people and people are such a mutual needs of the relationship. The more difficult the moment, the more we each need to take a step forward, each step out of a small step, will bring more confidence to each other.

##04

##It's good to be trusted, from being told to put away Wuhan ID cards to children's salutes

I remember the day after my probation ended, I went out to town with my father to buy medicine. When I checked out to show my ID card, someone advised me to put away my Wuhan ID card. When I offered to help, I was also declined to say, "I'll contact you when I need help. ".

At that moment, my heart has a kind of indescribable feeling, perhaps is bitter? I think people in Hubei Province inevitably have this kind of sentiment toward Wuhan, and I can't imagine what Wuhan is like now.

When I first started shopping, my dad would go with me. Many people don't understand us when they come to us to count our material needs. They even ask, "do you get paid? " "How much do I pay you for a month? " "Are you overpaying for this? " Hearing these words, my heart is very bad taste.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Xu Qing visits the villagers in his father's "convertible. " 

At the beginning of the supermarket materials shortage, commonly used items often given to this, the lack of that, we have a lot of blame. Most exaggerated, some people buy bags of Shiitake mushrooms are not fresh, good foam torn with us after the return, and then to the village cadres "inform. ". We've been working hard all day, and we might be able to pay him off later.

Fortunately, over time, we have a more reasonable method of material distribution, the village people gradually understand our work. Every day home statistics, the children will be excited around me in a circle, looking at my arm with the Red Armband, seriously give me a salute, very cute. Now, sooner or later, when we knock on the door, everyone smiles and says a few jokes.

It's good to live a simple life.

Isn't that what people do with each other? If you can give each other a little more trust, a little more understanding, a lot of things will be a lot easier, it will be easier.

Dull but busy day after a month, stay in Wuhan colleagues have also started to resume work at home. I also want to go back to Wuhan, where I have a home, I care about the friends. Wuhan is still under siege, I was so helpless outside the siege, siege life I still can not imagine.

I want to take off my mask one day earlier and go back to Wuhan to see the people I want to see. At that moment of our smiles will be very beautiful!

##05

##Conclusion: Wait for spring

On the last day of February, I photographed the broad bean blossoms in my old yard, and spring came. Sister Shi's parents have been cured and discharged from the hospital, the symptoms of the less sister Shi in the final observation. Friends see familiar teammates, the offspring of the national wrestling team began to go abroad to prepare for the Fiba World Olympic Qualifying Tournament, the march into the Tokyo Olympics. Yes, there is not a winter insurmountable, there is not a spring will not come.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The broad beans in the yard are in bloom

This year is a leap year, sports people also used to use the "four" multiple to mark the year. Let's hope that four years from now, when everyone looks back on this day, they will still be grateful.
